# Import Job Test Workflow

When the user asks to **start the import job** and **use Chrome automation to view the log progress** (or equivalent: “run import and watch progress”, “test import with browser”), follow this workflow and **fix errors, kill, build, repeat until it works**.

## 1. Kill all local running processes related to the project

- Stop any running `dotnet` processes (Web API, Import Service, Alert Agent).
- Ensure no process is locking project binaries so the build can succeed.

## 2. Compile all projects

- Run a full build of the solution (e.g. `dotnet build GenericLogHandler.sln`).
- If the build fails, fix the errors and repeat from step 1.

## 3. Start Web API and Import Service

- Start the Generic Log Handler **Web API** in the background (e.g. `dotnet run --no-build` from the WebApi project).
- Wait a few seconds for the API to listen.
- Start the **Import Service** (e.g. `dotnet run --no-build` from the ImportService project, in a separate process or window).

## 4. Use Chrome to view log progress

- Open **Chrome** (or the default browser) to the page that shows import/log progress:
  - **Import Status**: `http://localhost:52421/import-status.html` (per-source status, last processed file/line).
  - Or **Dashboard**: `http://localhost:52421/` (summary counts).
- Prefer the HTTP URL from launchSettings (e.g. `http://localhost:52421`) to avoid certificate warnings.
- If Chrome is installed in the default location, use `C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe` with the URL as argument; otherwise use `Start-Process` with the URL to open the default browser.

## 5. Fix errors and repeat until it works

- If the Import Service or Web API logs show errors, or the browser page shows failures:
  - **Fix** the code (config, connection strings, schema, or application logic as needed).
  - **Kill** all project-related processes again.
  - **Build** the solution again.
  - **Restart** Web API and Import Service, then **open Chrome** to the progress page again.
- Repeat this cycle until the import runs and progress is visible in the browser without errors.

Do not stop after one attempt if there are errors; keep fixing, killing, building, and restarting until the import job and log progress view work.
